Package seng201.islandtradergame.core

Class Ship

java.lang.Object
seng201.islandtradergame.core.Ship
public class Ship
extends java.lang.Object
This class implements a Ship which contains the traders bought items and can have have more capacity and travel faster depending on the ship created.

  • Constructor Details

    • Ship

      public Ship​(java.lang.String name, int speed, int capacity, int crewNum, int endurance)
      Creates a ship with a name, speed, capacity, crew and endurance.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of ship they user inputed in the main menu
      speed - The speed of the ship selected from the main menu can be (1 - 4)
      capacity - The ship capacity selected can be (100kL - 400kL)
      crewNum - The number of crew on the ship
      endurance - How resilient the ship is against damage

  • Method Details

    • sellItem

      public boolean sellItem​(Item item, Island island)
      Checks if the player has currently got the item they want to sell. This is done by checking if the objects have the same name. When the item is found it is updated with the island it was sold on and added to the sold items list. The item is removed from the cargo list and the ships capacity is updated to have the current capacity plus the size of the item.
      Parameters:
      item - The item the player is trying to sell
      island - The island the player is currently on
      Returns:
      boolean This is true when a sale is successful and false when the player does not have the item

    • buyItem

      public boolean buyItem​(Item item)
      Checks if the player has enough capacity left by comparing the size of the item to the ships current capacity. When they have enough space the ships capacity is updated by removing the size of the item from the current capacity. A new item object is created containing only a name, this is then added to the cargo list.
      Parameters:
      item - The item the player has selected to buy
      Returns:
      boolean This either states you have bought the item or you don't have enough space.
